# Gold Miner (Unity + C#)

A physics-based arcade game inspired by classic Gold Miner mechanics.  
The player uses a swinging claw to grab objects with different weights and values.

---

## Gameplay Overview

The player controls a rotating claw that automatically extends and retracts to grab objects such as gold, rocks, and other items.

Each object has different:
- weight
- pull speed
- score value

The goal is to reach the target score before time runs out.

---

## Core Features

- Physics-based claw grabbing system
- Swinging motion with timing mechanics
- Multiple object types (gold, rock, etc.)
- Score system based on object value
- Round-based gameplay loop
- Simple UI (score / timer / win-lose state)

---

## Technical Highlights

### Physics System
- Unity Rigidbody / Collider-based interaction
- Distance-based pulling behavior
- Object weight affects pull speed

### Claw System
- Rotating pivot-based swing system
- Auto extend / retract cycle
- Collision-triggered grab logic

### Gameplay Loop
- Timer-based rounds
- Score target system
- Win / Lose state handling

### 🧩 Architecture
- GameManager controls game state
- ClawController handles movement + grabbing
- Object scripts define behavior & value

